#: ../source/release-notes/3.0-scram.txt:18
msgid ""
"Starting in version 3.0, MongoDB includes support for the :ref:`Salted "
"Challenge Response Authentication Mechanism (SCRAM) <authentication-"
"scram>`, which changes how MongoDB uses and stores user credentials."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/release-notes/3.0-scram.txt:23
msgid ""
"If you are starting with a new 3.0+ deployment without any users or "
"upgrading from a 2.6 database that has no users, **no authentication "
"schema upgrade to SCRAM is required**. All newly created users will have "
"the correct format for SCRAM."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/release-notes/3.0-scram.txt:28
msgid ""
"For 3.0+ deployments with existing MongoDB Challenge and Response "
"(MONGODB-CR) user data model, the following procedure upgrades the "
"authentication schema to SCRAM."
